240/* Platform-specific calling convention macros.
241 *
242 * Platforms should define these so that Vulkan clients call Vulkan commands
243 * with the same calling conventions that the Vulkan implementation expects.
244 *
245 * VKAPI_ATTR - Placed before the return type in function declarations.
246 * Useful for C++11 and GCC/Clang-style function attribute syntax.
247 * VKAPI_CALL - Placed after the return type in function declarations.
248 * Useful for MSVC-style calling convention syntax.
249 * VKAPI_PTR - Placed between the '(' and '*' in function pointer types.
250 *
251 * Function declaration: VKAPI_ATTR void VKAPI_CALL vkCommand(void);
252 * Function pointer type: typedef void (VKAPI_PTR *PFN_vkCommand)(void);
253 */
254#if defined(_WIN32)
255 /* On Windows, Vulkan commands use the stdcall convention */
256 #define VKAPI_ATTR
257 #define VKAPI_CALL __stdcall
258 #define VKAPI_PTR VKAPI_CALL
259#elif defined(__ANDROID__) && defined(__ARM_ARCH) && __ARM_ARCH < 7
260 #error "Vulkan is not supported for the 'armeabi' NDK ABI"
261#elif defined(__ANDROID__) && defined(__ARM_ARCH) && __ARM_ARCH >= 7 && defined(__ARM_32BIT_STATE)
262 /* On Android 32-bit ARM targets, Vulkan functions use the "hardfloat" */
263 /* calling convention, i.e. float parameters are passed in registers. This */
264 /* is true even if the rest of the application passes floats on the stack, */
265 /* as it does by default when compiling for the armeabi-v7a NDK ABI. */
266 #define VKAPI_ATTR __attribute__((pcs("aapcs-vfp")))
267 #define VKAPI_CALL
268 #define VKAPI_PTR VKAPI_ATTR
269#else
270 /* On other platforms, use the default calling convention */
271 #define VKAPI_ATTR
272 #define VKAPI_CALL
273 #define VKAPI_PTR
274#endif
275

328/* DEPRECATED: This define is deprecated. VK_MAKE_API_VERSION should be used instead. */
329#define VK_MAKE_VERSION(major, minor, patch) \
330 ((((uint32_t)(major)) << 22) | (((uint32_t)(minor)) << 12) | ((uint32_t)(patch)))
331/* DEPRECATED: This define is deprecated. VK_API_VERSION_MAJOR should be used instead. */
332#define VK_VERSION_MAJOR(version) ((uint32_t)(version) >> 22)
333/* DEPRECATED: This define is deprecated. VK_API_VERSION_MINOR should be used instead. */
334#define VK_VERSION_MINOR(version) (((uint32_t)(version) >> 12) & 0x3FFU)
335/* DEPRECATED: This define is deprecated. VK_API_VERSION_PATCH should be used instead. */
336#define VK_VERSION_PATCH(version) ((uint32_t)(version) & 0xFFFU)
337#define VK_MAKE_API_VERSION(variant, major, minor, patch) \
338 ((((uint32_t)(variant)) << 29) | (((uint32_t)(major)) << 22) | (((uint32_t)(minor)) << 12) | ((uint32_t)(patch)))
339#define VK_API_VERSION_VARIANT(version) ((uint32_t)(version) >> 29)
340#define VK_API_VERSION_MAJOR(version) (((uint32_t)(version) >> 22) & 0x7FU)
341#define VK_API_VERSION_MINOR(version) (((uint32_t)(version) >> 12) & 0x3FFU)
342#define VK_API_VERSION_PATCH(version) ((uint32_t)(version) & 0xFFFU)

3935
3936static int glad_vk_get_extensions( VkPhysicalDevice physical_device, uint32_t *out_extension_count, char ***out_extensions) {
3937 uint32_t i;
3938 uint32_t instance_extension_count = 0;
3939 uint32_t device_extension_count = 0;
3940 uint32_t max_extension_count = 0;
3941 uint32_t total_extension_count = 0;
3942 char **extensions = NULL;
3943 VkExtensionProperties *ext_properties = NULL;
3944 VkResult result;
3945
3946 if (glad_vkEnumerateInstanceExtensionProperties == NULL || (physical_device != NULL && glad_vkEnumerateDeviceExtensionProperties == NULL)) {
3947 return 0;
3948 }
3949
3950 result = glad_vkEnumerateInstanceExtensionProperties(NULL, &instance_extension_count, NULL);
3951 if (result != VK_SUCCESS) {
3952 return 0;
3953 }
3954
3955 if (physical_device != NULL) {
3956 result = glad_vkEnumerateDeviceExtensionProperties(physical_device, NULL, &device_extension_count, NULL);
3957 if (result != VK_SUCCESS) {
3958 return 0;
3959 }
3960 }
3961
3962 total_extension_count = instance_extension_count + device_extension_count;
3963 if (total_extension_count <= 0) {
3964 return 0;
3965 }
3966
3967 max_extension_count = instance_extension_count > device_extension_count
3968 ? instance_extension_count : device_extension_count;
3969
3970 ext_properties = (VkExtensionProperties*) malloc(max_extension_count * sizeof(VkExtensionProperties));
3971 if (ext_properties == NULL) {
3972 goto glad_vk_get_extensions_error;
3973 }
3974
3975 result = glad_vkEnumerateInstanceExtensionProperties(NULL, &instance_extension_count, ext_properties);
3976 if (result != VK_SUCCESS) {
3977 goto glad_vk_get_extensions_error;
3978 }
3979
3980 extensions = (char**) calloc(total_extension_count, sizeof(char*));
3981 if (extensions == NULL) {
3982 goto glad_vk_get_extensions_error;
3983 }
3984
3985 for (i = 0; i < instance_extension_count; ++i) {
3986 VkExtensionProperties ext = ext_properties[i];
3987
3988 size_t extension_name_length = strlen(ext.extensionName) + 1;
3989 extensions[i] = (char*) malloc(extension_name_length * sizeof(char));
3990 if (extensions[i] == NULL) {
3991 goto glad_vk_get_extensions_error;
3992 }
3993 memcpy(extensions[i], ext.extensionName, extension_name_length * sizeof(char));
3994 }
3995
3996 if (physical_device != NULL) {
3997 result = glad_vkEnumerateDeviceExtensionProperties(physical_device, NULL, &device_extension_count, ext_properties);
3998 if (result != VK_SUCCESS) {
3999 goto glad_vk_get_extensions_error;
4000 }
4001
4002 for (i = 0; i < device_extension_count; ++i) {
4003 VkExtensionProperties ext = ext_properties[i];
4004
4005 size_t extension_name_length = strlen(ext.extensionName) + 1;
4006 extensions[instance_extension_count + i] = (char*) malloc(extension_name_length * sizeof(char));
4007 if (extensions[instance_extension_count + i] == NULL) {
4008 goto glad_vk_get_extensions_error;
4009 }
4010 memcpy(extensions[instance_extension_count + i], ext.extensionName, extension_name_length * sizeof(char));
4011 }
4012 }
4013
4014 free((void*) ext_properties);
4015
4016 *out_extension_count = total_extension_count;
4017 *out_extensions = extensions;
4018
4019 return 1;
4020
4021glad_vk_get_extensions_error:
4022 free((void*) ext_properties);
4023 if (extensions != NULL) {
4024 for (i = 0; i < total_extension_count; ++i) {
4025 free((void*) extensions[i]);
4026 }
4027 free(extensions);
4028 }
4029 return 0;
4030}
4031
4032static void glad_vk_free_extensions(uint32_t extension_count, char **extensions) {
4033 uint32_t i;
4034
4035 for(i = 0; i < extension_count ; ++i) {
4036 free((void*) (extensions[i]));
4037 }
4038
4039 free((void*) extensions);
4040}
4041
4042static int glad_vk_has_extension(const char *name, uint32_t extension_count, char **extensions) {
4043 uint32_t i;
4044
4045 for (i = 0; i < extension_count; ++i) {
4046 if(extensions[i] != NULL && strcmp(name, extensions[i]) == 0) {
4047 return 1;
4048 }
4049 }
4050
4051 return 0;
4052}
4053
4054static GLADapiproc glad_vk_get_proc_from_userptr(void *userptr, const char* name) {
4055 return (GLAD_GNUC_EXTENSION (GLADapiproc (*)(const char *name)) userptr)(name);
4056}
4057
4058static int glad_vk_find_extensions_vulkan( VkPhysicalDevice physical_device) {
4059 uint32_t extension_count = 0;
4060 char **extensions = NULL;
4061 if (!glad_vk_get_extensions(physical_device, &extension_count, &extensions)) return 0;
4062
4063 GLAD_VK_EXT_debug_report = glad_vk_has_extension("VK_EXT_debug_report", extension_count, extensions);
4064 GLAD_VK_EXT_debug_utils = glad_vk_has_extension("VK_EXT_debug_utils", extension_count, extensions);
4065 GLAD_VK_EXT_scalar_block_layout = glad_vk_has_extension("VK_EXT_scalar_block_layout", extension_count, extensions);
4066 GLAD_VK_EXT_validation_features = glad_vk_has_extension("VK_EXT_validation_features", extension_count, extensions);
4067 GLAD_VK_KHR_get_physical_device_properties2 = glad_vk_has_extension("VK_KHR_get_physical_device_properties2", extension_count, extensions);
4068 GLAD_VK_KHR_portability_enumeration = glad_vk_has_extension("VK_KHR_portability_enumeration", extension_count, extensions);
4069 GLAD_VK_KHR_shader_subgroup_extended_types = glad_vk_has_extension("VK_KHR_shader_subgroup_extended_types", extension_count, extensions);
4070 GLAD_VK_KHR_surface = glad_vk_has_extension("VK_KHR_surface", extension_count, extensions);
4071 GLAD_VK_KHR_swapchain = glad_vk_has_extension("VK_KHR_swapchain", extension_count, extensions);
4072#if defined(VK_USE_PLATFORM_WIN32_KHR)
4073 GLAD_VK_KHR_win32_surface = glad_vk_has_extension("VK_KHR_win32_surface", extension_count, extensions);
4074
4075#endif
4076#if defined(VK_USE_PLATFORM_XCB_KHR)
4077 GLAD_VK_KHR_xcb_surface = glad_vk_has_extension("VK_KHR_xcb_surface", extension_count, extensions);
4078
4079#endif
4080
4081 (void) glad_vk_has_extension;
4082
4083 glad_vk_free_extensions(extension_count, extensions);
4084
4085 return 1;
4086}
4087
4088static int glad_vk_find_core_vulkan( VkPhysicalDevice physical_device) {
4089 int major = 1;
4090 int minor = 0;
4091
4092#ifdef VK_VERSION_1_1
4093 if (glad_vkEnumerateInstanceVersion != NULL) {
4094 uint32_t version;
4095 VkResult result;
4096
4097 result = glad_vkEnumerateInstanceVersion(&version);
4098 if (result == VK_SUCCESS) {
4099 major = (int) VK_VERSION_MAJOR(version);
4100 minor = (int) VK_VERSION_MINOR(version);
4101 }
4102 }
4103#endif
4104
4105 if (physical_device != NULL && glad_vkGetPhysicalDeviceProperties != NULL) {
4106 VkPhysicalDeviceProperties properties;
4107 glad_vkGetPhysicalDeviceProperties(physical_device, &properties);
4108
4109 major = (int) VK_VERSION_MAJOR(properties.apiVersion);
4110 minor = (int) VK_VERSION_MINOR(properties.apiVersion);
4111 }
4112
4113 GLAD_VK_VERSION_1_0 = (major == 1 && minor >= 0) || major > 1;
4114
4115 return GLAD_MAKE_VERSION(major, minor);
4116}
4117
4118int gladLoadVulkanUserPtr( VkPhysicalDevice physical_device, GLADuserptrloadfunc load, void *userptr) {
4119 int version;
4120
4121#ifdef VK_VERSION_1_1
4122 glad_vkEnumerateInstanceVersion = (PFN_vkEnumerateInstanceVersion) load(userptr, "vkEnumerateInstanceVersion");
4123#endif
4124 version = glad_vk_find_core_vulkan( physical_device);
4125 if (!version) {
4126 return 0;
4127 }
4128
4129 glad_vk_load_VK_VERSION_1_0(load, userptr);
4130
4131 if (!glad_vk_find_extensions_vulkan( physical_device)) return 0;
4132 glad_vk_load_VK_EXT_debug_report(load, userptr);
4133 glad_vk_load_VK_EXT_debug_utils(load, userptr);
4134 glad_vk_load_VK_KHR_get_physical_device_properties2(load, userptr);
4135 glad_vk_load_VK_KHR_surface(load, userptr);
4136 glad_vk_load_VK_KHR_swapchain(load, userptr);
4137#if defined(VK_USE_PLATFORM_WIN32_KHR)
4138 glad_vk_load_VK_KHR_win32_surface(load, userptr);
4139
4140#endif
4141#if defined(VK_USE_PLATFORM_XCB_KHR)
4142 glad_vk_load_VK_KHR_xcb_surface(load, userptr);
4143
4144#endif
4145
4146
4147 return version;
4148}

4150
4151int gladLoadVulkan( VkPhysicalDevice physical_device, GLADloadfunc load) {
4152 return gladLoadVulkanUserPtr( physical_device, glad_vk_get_proc_from_userptr, GLAD_GNUC_EXTENSION (void*) load);
4153}

4173
4174static void* glad_get_dlopen_handle(const char *lib_names[], int length) {
4175 void *handle = NULL;
4176 int i;
4177
4178 for (i = 0; i < length; ++i) {
4179#if GLAD_PLATFORM_WIN32
4180 #if GLAD_PLATFORM_UWP
4181 size_t buffer_size = (strlen(lib_names[i]) + 1) * sizeof(WCHAR);
4182 LPWSTR buffer = (LPWSTR) malloc(buffer_size);
4183 if (buffer != NULL) {
4184 int ret = MultiByteToWideChar(CP_ACP, 0, lib_names[i], -1, buffer, buffer_size);
4185 if (ret != 0) {
4186 handle = (void*) LoadPackagedLibrary(buffer, 0);
4187 }
4188 free((void*) buffer);
4189 }
4190 #else
4191 handle = (void*) LoadLibraryA(lib_names[i]);
4192 #endif
4193#else
4194 handle = dlopen(lib_names[i], RTLD_LAZY | RTLD_LOCAL);
4195#endif
4196 if (handle != NULL) {
4197 return handle;
4198 }
4199 }
4200
4201 return NULL;
4202}
4203
4204static void glad_close_dlopen_handle(void* handle) {
4205 if (handle != NULL) {
4206#if GLAD_PLATFORM_WIN32
4207 FreeLibrary((HMODULE) handle);
4208#else
4209 dlclose(handle);
4210#endif
4211 }
4212}
4213
4214static GLADapiproc glad_dlsym_handle(void* handle, const char *name) {
4215 if (handle == NULL) {
4216 return NULL;
4217 }
4218
4219#if GLAD_PLATFORM_WIN32
4220 return (GLADapiproc) GetProcAddress((HMODULE) handle, name);
4221#else
4222 return GLAD_GNUC_EXTENSION (GLADapiproc) dlsym(handle, name);
4223#endif
4224}
4225
4226#endif /* GLAD_LOADER_LIBRARY_C_ */

4368
4369static int glad_vulkan_is_device_function(const char *name) {
4370 /* Exists as a workaround for:
4371 * https://github.com/KhronosGroup/Vulkan-LoaderAndValidationLayers/issues/2323
4372 *
4373 * `vkGetDeviceProcAddr` does not return NULL for non-device functions.
4374 */
4375 int i;
4376 int length = sizeof(DEVICE_FUNCTIONS) / sizeof(DEVICE_FUNCTIONS[0]);
4377
4378 for (i=0; i < length; ++i) {
4379 if (strcmp(DEVICE_FUNCTIONS[i], name) == 0) {
4380 return 1;
4381 }
4382 }
4383
4384 return 0;
4385}
4386
4387struct _glad_vulkan_userptr {
4388 void *vk_handle;
4389 VkInstance vk_instance;
4390 VkDevice vk_device;
4391 PFN_vkGetInstanceProcAddr get_instance_proc_addr;
4392 PFN_vkGetDeviceProcAddr get_device_proc_addr;
4393};
4394
4395static GLADapiproc glad_vulkan_get_proc(void *vuserptr, const char *name) {
4396 struct _glad_vulkan_userptr userptr = *(struct _glad_vulkan_userptr*) vuserptr;
4397 PFN_vkVoidFunction result = NULL;
4398
4399 if (userptr.vk_device != NULL && glad_vulkan_is_device_function(name)) {
4400 result = userptr.get_device_proc_addr(userptr.vk_device, name);
4401 }
4402
4403 if (result == NULL && userptr.vk_instance != NULL) {
4404 result = userptr.get_instance_proc_addr(userptr.vk_instance, name);
4405 }
4406
4407 if(result == NULL) {
4408 result = (PFN_vkVoidFunction) glad_dlsym_handle(userptr.vk_handle, name);
4409 }
4410
4411 return (GLADapiproc) result;
4412}

4414
4415static void* _vulkan_handle;
4416
4417static void* glad_vulkan_dlopen_handle(void) {
4418 static const char *NAMES[] = {
4419#if GLAD_PLATFORM_APPLE
4420 "libvulkan.1.dylib",
4421#elif GLAD_PLATFORM_WIN32
4422 "vulkan-1.dll",
4423 "vulkan.dll",
4424#else
4425 "libvulkan.so.1",
4426 "libvulkan.so",
4427#endif
4428 };
4429
4430 if (_vulkan_handle == NULL) {
4431 _vulkan_handle = glad_get_dlopen_handle(NAMES, sizeof(NAMES) / sizeof(NAMES[0]));
4432 }
4433
4434 return _vulkan_handle;
4435}
4436
4437static struct _glad_vulkan_userptr glad_vulkan_build_userptr(void *handle, VkInstance instance, VkDevice device) {
4438 struct _glad_vulkan_userptr userptr;
4439 userptr.vk_handle = handle;
4440 userptr.vk_instance = instance;
4441 userptr.vk_device = device;
4442 userptr.get_instance_proc_addr = (PFN_vkGetInstanceProcAddr) glad_dlsym_handle(handle, "vkGetInstanceProcAddr");
4443 userptr.get_device_proc_addr = (PFN_vkGetDeviceProcAddr) glad_dlsym_handle(handle, "vkGetDeviceProcAddr");
4444 return userptr;
4445}
4446
4447int gladLoaderLoadVulkan( VkInstance instance, VkPhysicalDevice physical_device, VkDevice device) {
4448 int version = 0;
4449 void *handle = NULL;
4450 int did_load = 0;
4451 struct _glad_vulkan_userptr userptr;
4452
4453 did_load = _vulkan_handle == NULL;
4454 handle = glad_vulkan_dlopen_handle();
4455 if (handle != NULL) {
4456 userptr = glad_vulkan_build_userptr(handle, instance, device);
4457
4458 if (userptr.get_instance_proc_addr != NULL && userptr.get_device_proc_addr != NULL) {
4459 version = gladLoadVulkanUserPtr( physical_device, glad_vulkan_get_proc, &userptr);
4460 }
4461
4462 if (!version && did_load) {
4463 gladLoaderUnloadVulkan();
4464 }
4465 }
4466
4467 return version;
4468}
4469
4470
4471
4472void gladLoaderUnloadVulkan(void) {
4473 if (_vulkan_handle != NULL) {
4474 glad_close_dlopen_handle(_vulkan_handle);
4475 _vulkan_handle = NULL;
4476 }
4477}
